						<summary>

						<p>The alphabet seems to be early, but the inscription is carelessly engraved. It records an endowment of 6(1/2) <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land after purchase by <hi rend="bold">Eḻuvaṉ Mādēvaṉ</hi> a merchant of Nandipuram, for feeding a Brāhmaṇa in the temple of Tirukkīḻkōṭṭam at Tirukkudamukkil after the daily mid-day service to the god. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
